        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 3:20PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 319 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Yost, or near Millboro, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Goshen...
Millboro...
Warm Springs...
Rockbridge Baths...
Nimrod Hall...
Bells Valley...
and Burnsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
